article.headline: Holy Cross 64, Lehigh 53
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass (AP) -- Torey Thomas scored 18 points and led a tenacious defense with seven steals as Holy Cross defeated Lehigh 64-53 Friday night. Jose Olivero scored 18 points to lead Lehigh (9-14, 4-3 Patriot League). Holy Cross (16-6, 7-0) won its ninth straight game and remained atop the league standings. Marquis Hall (11 points) and Olivero had 3-pointer to give the Mountain Hawks a 6-0 lead. But Holy Cross immediately answered with a nine-point run with Thomas getting a 3-pointer for a 9-6 lead. Holy Cross led 32-26 at the half. Keith Simmons (16 points) scored five points to extend the Crusaders' lead to 46-35 wih 12:06 left in the game. But Lehigh rallied. A 3-pointer by Matt Szalachowski cut the lead to 48-42 and then Olivero added four points in a 9-3 surge to make it 54-51. Holy Cross stayed in front, relying on its defense, which produced 16 steals. Pat Doherty and Tim Clifford scored to give the Crusaders a 56-51 lead with 3:46 left. The Crusaders held Lehigh scoreless for 4:28. Thomas, who also had eight assists, converted two free throws to give the Crusaders a 58-51 lead with :43 left.
